A vintage 1960s Singapore cityscape at dusk, featuring the Grand Hyatt hotel area with warm amber streetlights reflecting off glass buildings. In the foreground, a diverse group of business professionals in retro attire gather around a circular table on an outdoor terrace, animated in discussion, with glowing connection lines subtly linking them like an invisible web. Paper documents and early computing devices scatter across the table. The sky transitions from deep orange to purple, with stylized geometric patterns suggesting early network diagrams floating like constellations above the skyline. Grainy film texture, muted jewel tones, and slight vignetting evoke authentic mid-century photography with a touch of technological mysticism.
